My own Darlings:
Your good de-scription of the Indian "revel" was greedily devoured - Many thanks for the trouble you took to share that wonder-ful experience with me. 
I would be so glad to hear from Enid and Hilda about their view of it! 
I am every day afraid you have been hairing too cold a time to be truly pro-fitable - But I hope my fear is not founded on actu-al fact. 
Day before yesterday Don Garner honked as he passed 

