Our house is terribly upset now owing to the fact that paint dries slowly these chilly damp days. 
Your dispatch made me feel you were nearing the end of your trip - I hope you will take time to really enjoy the Black Hills etc. The grass in our pasture is so tall we have to have it cut. We have a godo man at 25 cents an hour. Combs remains away since he found I wanted him next to work out his debt. Your garden is ocming O.K, but not very slick. I am going to work in it this afternoon. The place looks like a bit of Heaven. I just mowed it again. 
